  "prompt": "In Japanese, what is the meaning of \"Kimigayo\"?",
  "response": "\"Kimigayo\" (\u541b\u304c\u4ee3) is the national anthem of Japan. The title translates to \"Thy Reign\" or \"Your Reign\" in English. The lyrics express wishes for the long reign of the emperor and convey themes of harmony and national unity. The anthem is known for its historical significance and is often played at official events in Japan.",
